Filtriranje višjih harmonikov iz zvočnega signala¶

Naložimo zvočni signal in prikažemo njegov potek v časovni domeni.

In [1]:
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from scipy.io import wavfile
from scipy.signal import find_peaks, butter, cheby1, cheby2, ellip, sosfilt, sosfreqz, freqz, lfilter, iirnotch
from numpy.fft import fft, fftfreq
from IPython.display import Audio, display

fMax = 2000

# sampleRate, signalData = wavfile.read("sounds/AHigh.wav")
# Audio: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4s7mlHrlS8w
sampleRate, signalData = wavfile.read("pianoG5.wav")

if signalData.ndim > 1:
    signalData = signalData[:, 0]
display(Audio(signalData, rate=sampleRate))
timeAxis = np.arange(len(signalData)) / sampleRate

plt.figure()
plt.plot(timeAxis, signalData)
plt.title("Raw Audio Signal")
plt.xlabel("Time [s]")
plt.ylabel("Amplitude")
plt.show()

Določanje osnovne frekvence¶

Funkcije za zaznavanje osnovne frekvence v signalu.

In [2]:
def estimateFundamentalFrequency(signal, sampleRate, fMin=50, fMax=fMax):
    N = len(signal)
    spectrum = np.abs(fft(signal))
    freqs = fftfreq(N, 1 / sampleRate)
    positiveFreqs = freqs[:N // 2]
    positiveSpectrum = spectrum[:N // 2]
    validMask = (positiveFreqs >= fMin) & (positiveFreqs <= fMax)
    validFreqs = positiveFreqs[validMask]
    validSpectrum = positiveSpectrum[validMask]
    peaks, _ = find_peaks(validSpectrum, height=np.max(validSpectrum) * 0.2, distance=sampleRate // fMin // 2)
    if len(peaks) == 0:
        print("no peaks detected")
        return None
    fundamentalFreq = validFreqs[peaks[0]]
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 4))
    plt.plot(validFreqs, validSpectrum)
    plt.plot(validFreqs[peaks], validSpectrum[peaks], 'rx')
    plt.title("FFT with peaks")
    plt.xlabel("Frekvenca (Hz)")
    plt.ylabel("Amplituda")
    plt.grid(True)
    plt.show()
    print(f"Estimated fundemental freq: {fundamentalFreq:.2f} Hz")

    return fundamentalFreq

def manualFundementalFrequency(signal, sampleRate):
    n = len(signal)
    freqAxis = fftfreq(n, d=1/sampleRate)
    fftSpectrum = np.abs(fft(signal))
    positiveFreqs = freqAxis > 0

    visualPeak = 294

    plt.figure()
    plt.plot(freqAxis[positiveFreqs & (freqAxis < fMax)], fftSpectrum[positiveFreqs & (freqAxis < fMax)])
    plt.title("FFT of Signal")
    plt.xlabel("Frequency [Hz]")
    plt.ylabel("Amplitude")
    plt.axvline(x=visualPeak, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Visual Peak: {visualPeak} Hz')
    plt.show()

    print(f"Manual fundemental frequency: {visualPeak:.2f} Hz")
    return visualPeak

Glavnični filter (Comb Filter)¶

Načrtovanje in uporaba glavničnega filtra za odstranjevanje višjih harmonikov nad 500 Hz.

In [4]:
harmonicsToRemove = [1, 2, 3, 6]
harmonicFreqs = [baseFreq * h for h in harmonicsToRemove if baseFreq * h > 500]
# harmonicFreqs = [baseFreq * h for h in harmonicsToRemove]

for freq in harmonicFreqs:
    print(f"Removing harmonic frequency: {freq:.1f} Hz")

n = len(signalData)
freqAxis = fftfreq(n, d=1/sampleRate)
fftSpectrum = np.abs(fft(signalData))
positiveFreqs = freqAxis > 0

def designCombFilter(freq, fs):
    quality = freq / 50
    w0 = freq / (fs / 2)
    b, a = iirnotch(w0, quality)
    return b, a

filteredComb = signalData.copy()
for freq in harmonicFreqs:
    b, a = designCombFilter(freq, sampleRate)
    filteredComb = lfilter(b, a, filteredComb)
    w, h = freqz(b, a, worN=2000, fs=sampleRate)
    plt.figure()
    mask = w < fMax
    plt.plot(w[mask], 20 * np.log10(abs(h[mask])))
    plt.title(f"Comb Filter Frequency Response at {freq:.1f} Hz")
    plt.xlabel("Frequency [Hz]")
    plt.ylabel("Magnitude [dB]")
    plt.grid()
    plt.show()

fftFilteredComb = np.abs(fft(filteredComb))
plt.figure()
plt.plot(freqAxis[positiveFreqs & (freqAxis < fMax)], fftSpectrum[positiveFreqs & (freqAxis < fMax)], label="Before")
plt.plot(freqAxis[positiveFreqs & (freqAxis < fMax)], fftFilteredComb[positiveFreqs & (freqAxis < fMax)], label="After Comb Filter")
plt.title("FFT Before and After Comb Filter")
plt.xlabel("Frequency [Hz]")
plt.ylabel("Amplitude")
plt.legend()
plt.show()

Removing harmonic frequency: 587.8 Hz
Removing harmonic frequency: 881.7 Hz
Removing harmonic frequency: 1763.4 Hz

Kaskadni filtri¶

Uporaba zaporednih filtrov za odstranjevanje posameznih harmonikov.

In [5]:
def designCascadeFilter(freq, fs, filterType="butter"):
    bw = 20
    low = (freq - bw/2) / (fs / 2)
    high = (freq + bw/2) / (fs / 2)
    if filterType == "butter":
        sos = butter(6, [low, high], btype="bandstop", output="sos")
    elif filterType == "cheby1":
        sos = cheby1(6, 1, [low, high], btype="bandstop", output="sos")
    elif filterType == "cheby2":
        sos = cheby2(6, 20, [low, high], btype="bandstop", output="sos")
    elif filterType == "ellip":
        sos = ellip(6, 1, 40, [low, high], btype="bandstop", output="sos")
    return sos

filteredCascade = signalData.copy()
for freq in harmonicFreqs:
    sos = designCascadeFilter(freq, sampleRate, "butter")
    filteredCascade = sosfilt(sos, filteredCascade)
    w, h = sosfreqz(sos, worN=2000, fs=sampleRate)
    mask = w < fMax
    plt.figure()
    plt.plot(w[mask], 20 * np.log10(abs(h[mask])))
    plt.title(f"Cascade Filter Frequency Response at {freq:.1f} Hz")
    plt.xlabel("Frequency [Hz]")
    plt.ylabel("Magnitude [dB]")
    plt.grid()
    plt.show()

fftFilteredCascade = np.abs(fft(filteredCascade))
plt.figure()
plt.plot(freqAxis[positiveFreqs & (freqAxis < fMax)], fftSpectrum[positiveFreqs & (freqAxis < fMax)], label="Before")
plt.plot(freqAxis[positiveFreqs & (freqAxis < fMax)], fftFilteredCascade[positiveFreqs & (freqAxis < fMax)], label="After Cascade Filter")
plt.title("FFT Before and After Cascade Filter")
plt.xlabel("Frequency [Hz]")
plt.ylabel("Amplitude")
plt.legend()
plt.show()

Učinek reda filtra na frekvenčno učinkovitost¶

Frekvenčni odziv filtrov različnih redov. Višji red pomeni ožji in globlji izrez frekvence.

In [7]:
testFreq = 800
orders = [2, 4, 6]

for order in orders:
    sos = butter(order, [(testFreq - 10) / (sampleRate / 2), (testFreq + 10) / (sampleRate / 2)], btype="bandstop", output="sos")
    w, h = sosfreqz(sos, worN=2000, fs=sampleRate)
    plt.plot(w, 20 * np.log10(abs(h)), label=f"Order {order}")

plt.title("Effect of Filter Order on Frequency Response")
plt.xlabel("Frequency [Hz]")
plt.ylabel("Magnitude [dB]")
plt.legend()
plt.grid(True)
plt.xlim(700, 900)
plt.show()

Odstranjevanje višjih harmonikov s kaskado filtrov¶

Tukaj primerjamo en sam filter z večfiltrsko kaskado za odstranjevanje več harmonikov.

Kaskada filtrov omogoča natančnejše izrezovanje točno določenih frekvenc.

In [8]:
singleFreq = 800
multiFreqs = [800, 1200, 1600]

sos_single = butter(6, [(singleFreq - 10)/(sampleRate/2), (singleFreq + 10)/(sampleRate/2)], btype='bandstop', output='sos')
w1, h1 = sosfreqz(sos_single, worN=2000, fs=sampleRate)

sos_combined = np.vstack([
    butter(6, [(f - 10)/(sampleRate/2), (f + 10)/(sampleRate/2)], btype='bandstop', output='sos')
    for f in multiFreqs
])
w2, h2 = sosfreqz(sos_combined, worN=2000, fs=sampleRate)

plt.plot(w1, 20 * np.log10(abs(h1)), label="Single Filter at 800 Hz")
plt.plot(w2, 20 * np.log10(abs(h2)), label="Cascade Filter at 800, 1200, 1600 Hz")
plt.title("Single vs. Cascaded Filters")
plt.xlabel("Frequency [Hz]")
plt.ylabel("Magnitude [dB]")
plt.grid(True)
plt.legend()
plt.xlim(600, 2000)
plt.show()

Primerjava: kaskada filtrov vs. frekvenčno filtriranje (FFT)¶

Kaskadni filtri omogočajo sprotno filtriranje v časovni domeni.

Frekvenčno filtriranje z FFT bi zahtevalo odseke, uporabo mask in inverzno transformacijo.

Kaskada je bolj fleksibilna in hitrejša za uporabo na zvoku v realnem času.
